profile_positions.description:
Activities: working independently and in teams on quantitative as well as qualitative research assignments. These assignments include: writing project proposals and (management) reports, designing and programming surveys, data gathering, statistical analysis, organising and chairing meetings with stakeholders, focus groups etc. Translating research findings into practical reccomendations and advising institutions, (local) governments and institutions how to implement these recommendations.  

Recent projects:
- Qualitative study; exploratory research with the aim to identify successful local/ regional policies to reduce educational disadvantages for specific target groups (children with different cultural backgrounds, delay in language development)
- A study to the results of specific educational instruments/ projects (summer schools, methods to reduce educational disadvantage and dropout);
- Study to determine the relation between alexithymia and somatisation and the mediating effect of depression;
- M&E study on cultural education (the results of cooperation between cultural institutions and schools);
- Impact study to the effects of extra school time on social-emotional development of children in primary school;
- Conducting statistical analysis on data files containing educational performance data;
- Organising and chairing group discussions amongst policy makers on several
educational/ social issues.

Project 2013-2014 (Barcelona):
An impact study to the effect of (elements of) digital newsletters on the attitudes and Internet behaviour (searching, purchasing) of recipients. Aim of this research was to: 1) discover general tendencies in the range and the effect of different means of communication with potential clients and 2) to determine the effect of specific newsletter characteristics (topics, competitions etc.).

Conducting statistical analysis on complex data files for several clients (local governments, hospitals, schoolboards etc.). Supporting organisations with the entire research process: designing, data collection, analysis, reporting and translating findings for policy makers.  

Activities:
- Processing statistical data​: summarizing and analysing information for M&E purposes (descriptive statistics);
- Analyzing relations between variables: (reliability analysis, analysis of variance, regression, discriminant and factor analysis);
- Reporting and translating the outcomes to meaningful information that can be used to improve and adjust policies; 
- Statistical consultation, training, counselling, organising workshops and seminars. 

Examples of studies conducted:
- A study to the attitude of inhabitants of Curacao (Caribbean) toward inhabitants with other cultural and ethnical backgrounds; what personal and contextual factors explain these attitudes;
- A study to the effect of leadership styles on corporate results and employee satisfaction;
- Several studies to determine employee satisfaction;
- A study commissioned by Mazars (accountancy) to the attitudes of clients toward
Corporate Social Responsibility.

Responsible for managing, editing and interpreting quantitative and qualitative data in the field of naturalising and participation for the local government of Rotterdam. Translating outcomes of research for policymakers and advising local government, administration and institutions in policy requirements based on the newest insights, derived from research in this field. 

Projects and responsibilities:
- Signalling developments, advising stakeholders based on these developments and forecasting future trends;
- Conducting research to the registration of data needed to determine policy success (M&E indicators);
- Advising government and administration officials on optimizing information management in the field of naturalisation and participation and implementing these improvements;
- Answering questions of government and administration officials concerning the results of policy in general and specific instruments.
